  "body": "Looks like abigen is broken after moving to latest solidity version.\r\nAll view methods are generated as transaction methods.\r\n\r\nfor example, this contract method:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\tfunction getDefaultXAndY() public view returns (uint x, uint y){\r\n\t\treturn (defaultX, defaultY);\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n```\r\nis generated as:\r\n```\r\n// GetDefaultXAndY is a paid mutator transaction binding the contract method 0xcd80054d.\r\n//\r\n// Solidity: function getDefaultXAndY() returns(uint256 x, uint256 y)\r\nfunc (_MyContract *MyContractTransactor) GetDefaultXAndY(opts *bind.TransactOpts) (*types.Transaction, error) {\r\n\treturn _My.contract.Transact(opts, \"getDefaultXAndY\")\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nLooks like this is a mismatch between abigen and solc.\r\nabigen is looking for \"constant\" file in the abi file, while the solc compiler creates:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\"inputs\":[]\r\n,\"name\":\"getDefaultXAndY\"\r\n,\"outputs\":[{\"internalType\":\"uint256\",\"name\":\"x\",\"type\":\"uint256\"},{\"internalType\":\"uint256\",\"name\":\"y\",\"type\":\"uint256\"}],\r\n\"stateMutability\":\"view\",\"type\":\"function\"\r\n},\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\na bypass to this problem is to manually update the abi file before running the abigen, and add field: constant:true\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Reproduce steps\r\nsolc --abi --output-dir ./compiled_contracts MyContract.sol\r\nsolc --bin --output-dir ./compiled_contracts MyContract.sol\r\ncd compiled_contracts\r\nabigen --bin MyContract.bin --abi MyContract.abi --pkg=my_contract --out=MyContract.go\r\n\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nsolc --version\r\nVersion: 0.6.0+commit.26b70077.Linux.g++\r\n\r\n abigen --version\r\nabigen version 1.9.9-stable-01744997\r\n\r\n",
